<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="109" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="109">Material examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="109">
5 specimens (107.5-129 mm SL), including the holotype, cited in 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith-Vaniz, WF" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Marine Science" pageId="29" pageNumber="124" pagination="1074 - 1128" title="Descriptions of five new species of jawfishes (Opistognathus: Opistognathidae) from the western Atlantic Ocean." volume="60" year="1997">Smith-Vaniz (1997)</bibRefCitation>
plus the following additional material: CIUFES 1459 (1, 64.0), Ilhas das 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Garças">Garcas</normalizedToken>
, Vila Velha, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Espírito">Espirito</normalizedToken>
Santo, 
<geoCoordinate direction="south" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="-20.6">20°36'S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate direction="west" orientation="longitude" precision="925" value="-40.366665">40°22'W</geoCoordinate>
, 30 March 2000, J.L. Gasparini.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="110" pageId="14" pageNumber="109" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="109">Distribution, habitat, and natural history.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="110" pageId="14" pageNumber="109">
A Brazilian endemic (Figure 6), known from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Espírito">Espirito</normalizedToken>
Santo to 
<normalizedToken originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
Paulo State, but absent from oceanic islands. A rare 
<pageBreakToken pageId="15" pageNumber="110" start="start">species</pageBreakToken>
only known from the type series collected in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="São">Sao</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Paulo’s">Paulo's</normalizedToken>
coastal waters (trawled in 50-69 m) and two specimens from Guarapari Islands, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Espírito">Espirito</normalizedToken>
Santo. Occurs in depths of 15-69 meters, associated with gravel and sand or silt and sand bottoms, near coral reefs and rocky areas.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="110" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="110">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="15" pageNumber="110">
In the diagnosis and description of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Opistognathidae" genus="Opistognathus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Opistognathus brasiliensis" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">Opistognathus brasiliensis</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith-Vaniz, WF" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Marine Science" pageId="29" pageNumber="124" pagination="1074 - 1128" title="Descriptions of five new species of jawfishes (Opistognathus: Opistognathidae) from the western Atlantic Ocean." volume="60" year="1997">Smith-Vaniz (1997)</bibRefCitation>
stated, in part, &quot;buccal pigmentation consisting of a dark area widely surrounding esophageal opening 
<normalizedToken originalValue="…”">...&quot;</normalizedToken>
versus area around esophageal opening pale in 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. cuvierii" pageId="15" pageNumber="110" rank="species" species="cuvierii">O. cuvierii</taxonomicName>
. This reported distinction is no longer valid because in a recently examined female specimen of 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Opistognathidae" genus="Opistognathus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Opistognathus brasiliensis" order="Perciformes" pageId="15" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">Opistognathus brasiliensis</taxonomicName>
(CIUFES 1459) the area around the esophageal opening is pale. Both species have black areas in front of each pharyngeal tooth patch that are separated by a pale median area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="110" type="conservation">
